Rating: 4
This was the sweetest biscotti recipe I've had. These were my modifications: * 1/2 C. Brown Sugar but 1/3 C. white sugar. * 1/2 tsp of vanilla with the 1/2 tsp almond extract. *2 C. Whole wheat flour *85% Cocoa (about 4 squares) of Lindt chocolate and 1 oz of good dark chocolate I keep hidden in my freezer. *1/2 tsp. Kosher salt (it was a bit too salty. Perhaps I'd cut it down further to 1/4. tsp.) *I also divided the dough in half before i kneaded in the dried fruit. 1/2 of it had 1/3 C. Dried Cranberries and the other half held 1/3 C. Dried Sour Cherries. (Orange zest would have went along well, but I have a similar scone recipe and wanted to diverge.) The result was a nice contrast with the chocolate and sweet biscuit. The tartness of the cherries was a good subtle interjection between too much sweet and chocolaty goodness. The cranberry version blended well together. I had them with a shot of espresso with a touch of my tasty coconut creme.

