I love these biscottis and co-workers seemed to really like them too! I was looking for a good basic biscotti recipe, and this was it. I substituted dried cherries for cranberries, and added chocolate chips. I also added a little extra almond extract. I didn't use the egg wash or drizzle chocolate. This is the type of recipe that you can flavor any way you want, and add whatever you please (vanilla, orange, lemon, nuts, dried fruits, chocolate...) I made this recipe once and the dough was too wet. As a result, the logs did not hold their shape. I made it a second time with an extra 1/2 cup of flour and this worked much better. I would recommend that the dough be a stiff cookie dough and add more flour as necessary. Enjoy!

